org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.config

Interface IWriteOnlyProjectSettings

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ICompilerSettings, IFlexProject
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Configurator, FlexJSProject, FlexProject, Optimizer.OptimizerConfigurator

    public interface IWriteOnlyProjectSettings
    Setters for Project settings that can come from command line compiler options. This interface is implemented by Configurator and IFlexProject to keep the common setters for these interfaces in sync.

    • Method Detail

      • setSourcePath

        void setSourcePath(List<File> paths)
        Sets a list of path elements that form the roots of ActionScript class hierarchies. Calling this method can invalidate a significant amount of incremental compilation results. This is equivalent to using mxmlc/compc --compiler.source-path.
        Parameters:
        paths - List of directories that should be searched for source files.

      • setLocales

        void setLocales(Collection<String> locales)
        Sets the locales that the compiler would use to replace {locale} tokens that appear in some configuration values. This is equivalent to using mxmlc/compc --compiler.locale. For example, The locale/en_US directory will be added to the source path.

      • setActionScriptFileEncoding

        void setActionScriptFileEncoding(String encoding)
        Sets the ActionScript file encoding. The compiler will use this encoding to read the ActionScript source files. This is equivalent to using mxmlc/compc --compiler.actionscript-file-encoding.

        By default, the encoding is UTF-8.

        Parameters:
        encoding - charactere encoding, e.g. UTF-8, Big5

      • setDefineDirectives

        void setDefineDirectives(Map<String,String> defines)
        Set global AS3 compiler configuration values and clear existing definitions. This is equivalent to using the mxmlc/compc --define option once for each definition in the map.
        Parameters:
        defines - A map of qualified names/configuration constants, e.g. "CONFIG::debugging" or "APP::version", to value constants, e.g. "true" or "!CONFIG::release" or "3.0". Null clears the existing definitions.

      • setCompatibilityVersion

        Sets the SDK compatibility version.
        Parameters:

        minor - The minor version.
        revision - The revision component of the version.

      • setNamespaceMappings

        void setNamespaceMappings(List<? extends IMXMLNamespaceMapping> namespaceMappings)
        Sets the mappings from MXML namespace URI to manifest files, as specified by -namespace options.
        Parameters:
        namespaceMappings - An array of MXMLNamespaceMapping objects.

      • setExtensionLibraries

        void setExtensionLibraries(Map<File,List<String>> extensions)
        Configures a list of many extensions mapped to a single Extension URI. something-extension.jar version=1.1,content=1.2 The extensions run at the end of a compilation.
        Parameters:
        extensions - a map of extension element files to extension paths.

      • setServicesXMLPath

        void setServicesXMLPath(String path,
                      String contextRoot)
        Configure this project to use a services-config.xml file. The services-config.xml file is used to configure a Flex client to talk to a BlazeDS server. This is equivalent to using mxmlc/compc --services and --context-root.
        Parameters:
        path - an absolute path to the services-config.xml file.
        contextRoot - sets the value of the {context.root} token, which is often used in channel definitions in the services-config.xml file.

      • setIncludeSources

        void setIncludeSources(Collection<File> sources)
                       throws InterruptedException
        A collection of source files or directories to add to the target library. This is equivalent to the include-sources option of the compc compiler.
        Parameters:
        sources - A collection of source files or directories.
        Throws:
        InterruptedException

      • setFlex

        void setFlex(boolean value)
        Option to enable or prevent various Flex compiler behaviors. This is currently used to enable/disable the generation of a root class for library swfs and generation of Flex specific code for application swfs.
        Parameters:
        value - true to turn on Flex behaviors, false otherwise.

      • setExcludeNativeJSLibraries

        void setExcludeNativeJSLibraries(boolean value)
        Option to remove the Native JS libraries from external-library-path and library-path as they shouldn't be any when compiling SWFs / SWCs.
        Parameters:
        value - true to turn on the behaviors, false otherwise.
